1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:4.68,000
Hook DuckDB vs. Overture Downloader. Same data, very different experience.

2
00:00:5.16,000 --> 00:00:9.02,000
Platform YouTube 16-X9. Duration 90s.

3
00:00:9.38,000 --> 00:00:15.24,000
Audience GS Analyst. Section 1. Setup 0.0.0.0.8.

4
00:00:15.64,000 --> 00:00:18.14,000
There are a few ways to get Overture Maps data.

5
00:00:18.46,000 --> 00:00:22.18,000
I'm going to show you two of them side by side so you can decide which fits your workflow.

6
00:00:22.18,000 --> 00:00:26.58,000
Section 2. The Hard Way 08040

7
00:00:26.58,000 --> 00:00:30.22,000
Method 1. The official Python CLI.

8
00:00:30.66,000 --> 00:00:35.44,000
Install overture maps via pip, look up your bounding box coordinates from a separate tool,

9
00:00:35.94,000 --> 00:00:42.16,000
format them as west-south-east-north, run the download command, specify your output format, wait.

10
00:00:42.84,000 --> 00:00:47.26,000
It works, but if your pip environment is broken or you haven't touched the terminal in a while,

11
00:00:47.6,000 --> 00:00:50.36,000
that quick data pull turns into a debugging session.

12
00:00:50.36,000 --> 00:00:56.82,000
Method 2. DuckDB. Write a SQL query against S3. Make sure your region is set correctly.

13
00:00:57.28,000 --> 00:00:59.74,000
Understand Geoparquet enough to export it properly.

14
00:01:0.4200000000000017,000 --> 00:01:4.560000000000002,000
Again, totally valid if that's your world, but it's a lot of setup for,

15
00:01:4.819999999999993,000 --> 00:01:6.540000000000006,000
I just need the roads for this district.

16
00:01:7.079999999999998,000 --> 00:01:10.5,000
Section 3. The Fast Way. 040-110

17
00:01:10.5,000 --> 00:01:17.560000000000002,000
Method 3. The Overture Downloader at hanko.com slash tools slash Overture Downloader.

18
00:01:17.560000000000002,000 --> 00:01:23.599999999999994,000
Open browser. Draw a rectangle on the map over your area. Pick your data set. Download.

19
00:01:24.5,000 --> 00:01:28.78,000
GeoJSON is in your folder in under a minute. Same Overture data. Zero setup.

20
00:01:29.36,000 --> 00:01:31.760000000000005,000
Section 4. Verdict 110-130.

21
00:01:32.42,000 --> 00:01:36.239999999999995,000
If you work with Overture regularly and live in the terminal, the CLI is great.

22
00:01:36.81999999999999,000 --> 00:01:41.459999999999994,000
If you need data quickly, you're on a shared computer, or you're handing this off to a non-developer,

23
00:01:41.459999999999994,000 --> 00:01:45.519999999999996,000
the browser tool is just faster. Both are free. Link to both in the description.